#14326
`6A`^e`&g`^i`6s `8I`7n`&n``~
The common area in the forfront of the Aegis Inn is quite large and
rather impressive due to a sleek design that segways the sections in the
room easily.  There is a bar counter to the north, with a massive mirror
behind the back wall in which a bottle of everything seems to be placed. 
The black painted oak counter glistens a little bit, as does the stools and
tables in the area.  To the west side of the room there are booths made of
the same glossy black oak.  The boothes themselves are purposely poorly lit
and private.  Against the east wall there is a fireplace with a nice rug
before it, followed by two cozy chairs that look the fireplace over.  There
is also a stairway up which passes by the harrowing rafters above.  
~
